The Commissioner of Police, Lagos State, Hakeem Odumosu, on Wednesday said he has tightened security around the metropolis over the decision of members of a secret cult group, Aiye confraternity, to mark July 7 day celebration. The group had set aside July 7 of every year to mark itâ€™s anniversary and carry out initiation ceremony on new members which is usually characterized by violence and killings. The command also assured on massive deployment of officers to curtail cult-related activities and forestall breakdown of law and order in the state. 